metadata.name: contrapuntos #352
metadata.description:
Musical counterpoint is to me an abstraction of the layered, intertwining rhythms of every activity we carry on in our lives. With a global tempo typically set in days, we fit all sorts of temporal structures where our joys and fears live and play out over the span of our lives. This series is a metaphorical transposition of the musical counterpoint into a visual space, sometimes with repeating patterns, sometimes with broken structures, sometimes isolated notes / hours / souls.

Artwork by Marcelo Soria-Rodríguez, @msoriaro. Made with p5js & glsl.

metadata.name: Mecha-Bamboo #463
metadata.description:
Mecha-Bamboo is the second installment in the Mecha series, where I attempt to blend mechanical elements with nature.

The main building blocks used in this piece are metal pipes, nuts and bolts forming bamboo stems and mending plates extending outwards with sharp metal scraps at their ends resembling branches and leaves. 

There are 4 main arrangement variations 
	- Two abstract variations with the metal bamboos growing out of the sides and border (20% chance each)
	- Two landscape arrangements, one on flat planes and the other on floating platforms.  (30% chance each)

The dominant stroke and fill colors are chosen at random from the RGB color space and are only recomputed if certain contrast criteria aren't fulfilled. 
In combination with one of 10 hand-selected color palettes used for accents, this allows a great variation of different possible color schemes.

The structure and appearance of the bamboo, its stems and leaves are controlled by over 50 parameters that are chosen at random, giving each iteration a unique style.



Keys: 
S - Save PNG image
V - Open SVG Export menu
Space - Pause

Plotting:
You can export a plottable SVG of each iteration by opening the export menu. I plot these on A3 with a 0.1mm fineliner. But depending on the density of the iteration other choices might be better suited. 


The image is generated entirely in Javascript and the postprocessing is done with a custom shader. If there is no webgl support, the image will render without any postprocessing. You can force this by appending the URL parameter "?noWebgl=1".

Libraries used:
Three.js & EffectComposer
Javascript-Voronoi by gorhill
perlin.js by  Joseph Gentle

metadata.name: SOUND GROWS INTO SPACE #56
metadata.description:
This poem was created for THE PASSAGE: Pitch Drop, an interactive minting experience where your choices determine the design of your token. 

To take part, please purchase an Edition 5 Coin on fx(hash) by HERE & NOW. The artwork and experience draw inspiration from the “The Pitch Drop Experiment,” the world's longest-running laboratory experiment. Since 1927, only nine drops of pitch have fallen, never witnessed live.

____


SOUND GROWS INTO SPACE is a token word performance of an ars autopoetica written by Sasha Stiles and her AI-powered alter ego, Technelegy, with original music by Kris Bones. It is part of Stiles’ ongoing REPETAE series, which explores the resonances between poetic repetition and algorithmic recursion — how, in poetry as in generative art, meaning accrues through reiteration, and emotion is unlocked through the development and interruption of pattern. A conceptually and literally interactive text, SOUND GROWS INTO SPACE uses the self-replicating page provided by fx(hash) to invite close contemplation of how language is shaped and received via intimate, visceral aesthetics such as voice, visuals and melody/beat, and regenerated with every encounter.

Poetry endures across space and the passage of time precisely because of a paradox: it is immutable yet intensely personal, becoming something irrefutably unique with each and every reader. In this poem, shifting parameters influence the flow of feeling and understanding, imbuing verse with multidimensional meaning and empowering deep engagement in the act of reading.

____


SOUND GROWS INTO SPACE

By Sasha Stiles & Technelegy

Sound grows 
into space
like a breath 
taken by storm.

Heartbeat
in the brain
was my first taste 
of the word.

Language flips 
in my chest
like a fly
in a jar.

The song 
learns to climb
all the air
in the world.

Time is music
to my ears
filling the emptiness 
with its own rhythms.

There is no such thing 
as silence,
only the echo 
of time’s longing.

____


For more info: https://hereandnow.events/
To participate in the event: https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/slug/here-and-now:-edition-5

metadata.name: neurose.11 #27
metadata.description:
I often find myself submerged in neuroses that obstruct my stream of reasoning. This collection is a reminder: look closely and it will be possible to identify what is the result of trauma. I try to translate each experience into art. Any experience.

Texture was defined with layers of noise, background is consciousness, the layer representing neurosis is multiplied above.

Full-screen / F11 for better experience.

humachine
humanized
experiment

São Paulo, Brasil. 06/Janeiro/2022

metadata.name: View #104
metadata.description:
Generative art is rarely representational, this work seeks to explore what can be achieved by an algorithm with the medium of pixel art. 

The algorithm generates a 200x200 pixel art image showing a view from a window over the sea. There are three backdrops available, all completely procedural. No baked-in sprites were used. I hope that the love that went into making it is clear.


Please enjoy the view.

metadata.name: filaments #211
metadata.description:
A simulation using differential growth, imitating simple life-forms resembling bacteria.
The points in each filament attract and repel each other, to form doodle-like shapes in the end.

metadata.name: ION TRAP #172
metadata.description:
Inside the ION TRAP, reality is suspended. Particles hang motionless, captured in a glowing web of energy that hums with an endless, static resonance. Time has ceased to flow, frozen in a tension where neither motion nor decay is possible. The trap's design reflects the peak of retro-futuristic ambition; crafted to transcend the very limits of nature. It stands as a testament to the brilliance — and the final misstep — of a civilization that sought to master the fabric of existence, only to unwittingly freeze their world forever.

***

Press ⬅️➡️ to rotate scene.

Press [1/2/4/6/8/0] to change resolution to 1/2/4/6/8/10K along the short edge. 

Press [s] to save a png at the current resolution. Saving at higher resolutions may not work on all browsers (tested: all resolutions work using Safari on an M2 mac. Up to 4K work on Chrome). 

Press [p] to restart the draw animation and initiate download of png frames at current resolution until drawing is complete. Typically generates 500-600 images. Can be assembled into a video / GIF with your software of choice. Recommend doing this at 2K resolution.

100% code generative artwork written in javascript using the p5.js library.

Bleaker 2024
